en its High lvl cousin lures Lightning,Fire,Ice even.. But if you can get a lure of ice off in time do it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .. I recommend frost from the rogue's hit rate ;p.. The backstab <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  actully its not really that hard to stop it involves a good wrist and somePrediction .. When I have a rogue on me I twerl the mouse before hand before he gets over me and twerls above my head for the backstab, try turning around while hes just about to go over your head  and still ahead of you.. If tanking aint your game you can also try hill bugging and Levitating over shit and nuking <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  which works much easier but It isnt very fair ;p.. All and all this will only help vs the rouge I doubt depending on the gear and skill of the rogue it will kill him before he kills you.. Rogue's are just the damn wizard bane class :P <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucalimike3000.showPublicProfile?language=EN>calimike3000</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/7/01 1:55:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm27.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=25>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ...</span><hr size=1> I'm slightly amused and a little interested in the argument as to what is fair in an open pvp fight.  <br>
<br>
Let's drop fair, though, and go for gentlemanly/acceptable.<br>
<br>
Acceptable:<br>
-Waiting until target isn't fighting a mob<br>
-Using terrain to your advantage<br>
-Using stupidity to your advantage<br>
-Using class abilities to your advantage<br>
-Sneak attacks<br>
-Ambushing (With a nice communication system, and a nice wizard, you could arrange some interesting surprises)<br>
<br>
Not acceptable:<br>
-Waiting until target is memmed to full after fighting a mob/Expecting others to not attack you immediately after you finish a fight<br>
-RunBys, or sniping a target when he's invis and near a mob that hates him<br>
-Wearing gear that's normally unobtainable by anyone within 20 levels of your current season (I expect a lot of argument on this one)<br>
-Bind rushing<br>
-Camping<br>
-Using game bugs to your advantage (bard-charm on pets, ducking in water)<br>
<br>
Comments?  Have I missed anything?<br>
